## 🗺️ Engineering Roadmap

### ✅ Phase 1: Foundation & Real-Time Sync (Completed)
- [x] Scaffold .NET 8 Minimal API.
- [x] Implement core game domain logic (State Machine, Win/Draw calculation).
- [x] Implement REST endpoints for session creation.
- [x] Integrate SignalR for WebSocket room management (`JoinGame`, `MakeMove`).
- [x] Build HTML/JS integration test client.

### ✅ Phase 2: Containerization (Completed)
- [x] Write `.dockerignore`.
- [x] Write Multi-Stage `Dockerfile`.
- [x] Verify local container networking and execution.

### 🚧 Phase 3: Cloud Native Deployment (Up Next)
- [ ] **AWS ECR:** Authenticate Docker CLI with AWS and push the image to Elastic Container Registry.
- [ ] **AWS Compute:** Deploy the container to AWS Lightsail or ECS Fargate.
- [ ] **CI/CD:** Set up GitHub Actions to automatically build and push the Docker image on `main` branch merges.

### 🔮 Phase 4: Persistence & Scaling (Future Architecture)
- [ ] **Database Migration:** Replace the in-memory `ConcurrentDictionary` with PostgreSQL using Entity Framework (EF) Core.
- [ ] **Orchestration:** Write `docker-compose.yml` to spin up the API and Postgres simultaneously for local dev.
- [ ] **Horizontal Scaling:** Integrate a **Redis Backplane** for SignalR. *(Crucial: If the API scales to multiple AWS instances, Redis ensures WebSocket messages are synced across all servers).*

