### How to use this moving forward:
Whenever you add a new piece of infrastructure (like the Postgres DB or the Redis backplane), you simply update the **Roadmap** and **Building Blocks** section of this README, and put the heavy, verbose configuration instructions into a separate markdown file in the `/docs` folder. 

This keeps your repository looking incredibly professional and immediately readable to other senior engineers or technical recruiters. 

Are we ready to tackle **Phase 3** and push this container up to your AWS environment?